{
  "texts": [
    "All the model's capabilities are already present after the pretraining stage [46].",
    "The postprocessing steps aim to reduce the raw model's propensity to produce toxic responses as well as to make it implement a consistent \"personality\" in accord with product design goals.",
    "These steps are not always entirely effective in preventing LLMs from producing undesirable behaviors like toxic or harmful language, and \"jailbreak\" prompts which trick the model into responding inappropriately are still easy to discover and implement [47, 48].",
    "Argyle et al. (2023) offered a suggestion for how to use LLMs in social science research.",
    "Given the correct conditioning, the authors argue that free-text output generated by large language models like GPT-3 can serve as effective proxies for specific human population groups."
  ]
}